{"word":"εὖγμα","slug":"εὖγμα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὖγμα</b></el> <el>(εὖγμα, ατος, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:εὔχομαι'><el>εὔχομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>like <el>εὖχος</el>, <i>a boast, vaunt</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>like <el>εὐχή</el>, but always in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>prayers, wishes</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}